      • clear

        public void clear()
        Description copied from class: JposErrorEvent
        Clears all input data or buffered output requests, error and output complete events that belong to thir error event. Neither ClearInput nor ClearOutput should throw an exception because both operations should be implemented as internal operations that do not need to throw and exception. However, if an implementation should throw a JposException, it will be caught and ignored.
